org.jitsi.videobridge

Class Videobridge

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jitsi.videobridge.Videobridge

  • public class Videobridge
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents the Jitsi Videobridge which creates, lists and destroys Conference instances.

        Constant Field Values

      • REST_API_PNAME

        public static final java.lang.String REST_API_PNAME
        The (base) System and/or ConfigurationService property of the REST-like HTTP/JSON API of Jitsi Videobridge. NOTE: Previously, the rest API name ("org.jitsi.videobridge.rest") conflicted with other values in the new config, since we have other properties scoped *under* "org.jitsi.videobridge.rest". The long term solution will be to port the command-line args to new config, but for now we rename the property used to signal the rest API is enabled so it doesn't conflict.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

        Initializes a new Conference instance with an ID unique to the Conference instances listed by this Videobridge and adds the new instance to the list of existing Conference instances.
        Parameters:
        name - world readable name of the conference to create.
        gid - the "global" id of the conference (or Conference#GID_NOT_SET if it is not specified.
        Returns:
        a new Conference instance with an ID unique to the Conference instances listed by this Videobridge

      • handleHealthCheckIQ

        public IQ handleHealthCheckIQ(HealthCheckIQ healthCheckIQ)
        Handles HealthCheckIQ by performing health check on this Videobridge instance.
        Parameters:
        healthCheckIQ - the HealthCheckIQ to be handled.
        Returns:
        IQ with "result" type if the health check succeeded or IQ with "error" type if something went wrong. XMPPError.Condition#internal_server_error is returned when the health check fails or XMPPError.Condition#not_authorized if the request comes from a JID that is not authorized to do health checks on this instance.

      • getDebugState

        public OrderedJsonObject getDebugState(java.lang.String conferenceId,
                                       java.lang.String endpointId,
                                       boolean full)
        Creates a JSON for debug purposes. If a specific conferenceId is requested, the result will include all of the state of the conference considered useful for debugging (note that this is a LOT of data). Otherwise (if conferenceId is null), the result includes a shallow list of the active conferences and their endpoints.
        Parameters:
        conferenceId - the ID of a specific conference to include. If not specified, a shallow list of all conferences will be returned.
        endpointId - the ID of a specific endpoint in conferenceId to include. If not specified, all of the conference's endpoints will be included.
